  <preface xml:id="preface-ptx-version">
    <title>Note on This PreTeXt Edition</title>

    <p>
      This is a <url href="https://pretextbook.org/" visual="pretextbook.org">PreTeXt</url>
      conversion of<em>Introduction to Data Science: Data Wrangling and Visualization with R</em>, originally written by
     <url href = "https://rafalab.dfci.harvard.edu/">Rafael A. Irizarry</url>.
      The original work is available online at
        <url href="https://rafalab.github.io/dsbook-part-2/" visual="rafalab.github.io/dsbook-part-2">rafalab.github.io/dsbook-part-2</url>
      and was published by CRC Press. The original GitHub repository for the book source is at
      <url href="https://github.com/rafalab/dsbook-part-2">github.com/rafalab/dsbook-part-2</url>.
    </p>

    <p>
        This PreTeXt edition was prepared by
        <url href="https://github.com/PreTeXtBooks/dataskills-part-2"
           visual="github.com/PreTeXtBooks/dataskills-part-2">the PreTeXtBooks project</url>
to make the content available in the PreTeXt format, enabling accessible and structured
      output in HTML, PDF, and other formats.   All prose, code examples, figures, and mathematical content are intended to be 
  faithful reproductions of the original work, though occasional typographical errors 
  may have been introduced in the conversion process. Report any issues to our
        <url href="https://github.com/PreTeXtBooks/dataskills-part-1/issues">GitHub Issues Page</url>.
      </p>

    <p>
      The original work by Rafael A. Irizarry is licensed under a
      <url href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International</url>.
    </p>
  </preface>

  <preface xml:id="preface">
    <title>Preface</title>
    <p>
      This is a PreTeXt version of the <em>Statistics and Prediction Algorithms Through Case Studies</em>, 
      the second part of <em>Introduction to Data Science</em>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The website for the first part, <em>Data Wrangling and Visualization with R</em>, is 
      <url href="http://rafalab.dfci.harvard.edu/dsbook-part-1/">here</url>, with the PreTeXt version 
      for the first part <url href="https://pretextbooks.github.io/dataskills-part-1/">here</url>.
    </p>
    <p>
      This book started out as part of the class notes used in the HarvardX 
      <url href="https://www.edx.org/professional-certificate/harvardx-data-science">Data Science Series</url>.
    </p>
    <p>
      A hardcopy version of the first edition of the book, which combined both parts, is available from 
      <url href="https://www.routledge.com/Introduction-to-Data-Science-Data-Wrangling-and-Visualization-with-R/Irizarry/p/book/9781032116556">CRC Press</url>.
    </p>
    <p>
      A free PDF of the October 24, 2019 version of the book, which combined both parts, is available from 
      <url href="https://leanpub.com/datasciencebook">Leanpub</url>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Quarto code used to generate the book is available on 
      <url href="https://github.com/rafalab/dsbook-part-2">GitHub</url>.
    </p>
    <p>
      This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International 
      <url href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</url>.
    </p>
    <p>
      We make announcements related to the book on X. For updates follow 
      <url href="https://x.com/rafalab">@rafalab</url>.
    </p>
  </preface>

